Author: hardik
Content:
After a lot of brain twisting it sinks in.. and I do probability for living!

For doubters: Before the door is opened by the host, you are less likely to have chosen the right one(with prob 1/3). Once he opens the door, he eliminates one "bad door". Now, given that you were less likely to have chosen the right one in the first place and one wrong one has been removed, it is highly likely that the residual door is the right one.

Author: DougBTX
Content:
How can you be told information about a particular child if you have no way to distinguish them?

I partially understand your point about G'g vs Gg' now: if having a prime is the only way to distinguish the children, then G and g must be indistinguishable, so G = g.
